cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper deals with clinical Named Entity Recognition (NER) and concept extraction from user queries. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for extracting clinical concepts, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely sub-category. The use of machine learning models for NER and concept extraction suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with clinical data, which could make cs.CY (Computers and Society) a relevant sub-category as well.
